The most common bug to avoid when implementing the rotate_matrix function is incorrectly handling the matrix dimensions and indices, leading to an IndexError or incorrect rotation. 

```python
def rotate_matrix(m):
    n = len(m)
    for i in range(n):
        for j in range(i, n):
            m[j][i], m[i][j] = m[i][j], m[j][i]
    for i in range(n):
        m[i] = m[i][::-1]
```
